from 21.00 - 01.04, spouts & animals in sight the whole time. The greatest cetacean show I have ever seen in Svalbard & a great way to sign off my season! Bear has collar. Walking in from south near Holmiabukta over the hill and into beach where the whale carcass used to be. She walked to the eastern side, looked like she wanted to swim. Instead she headed back to south side and started swimming across the bay, turned left just before land, and continued swimming into Sallyhamna. She got out of the water on the SW side of the bay turned left towards sallyhamna. A sysselmann came walking along the shore on the opposite side; east side of the bay. He shot his signal pistol. The bear ran about 5 meters away from the direction of the sysselmann, looking at the direction where the flare had gone off, sniffed the air. She then stood still for a very long time, possible 5-10 minutes. She moved slowly Eeast up the hill and into a little Auk colony where she sniffed around for the next hour. Finally she disappeared behind a big boulder and we did not see her anymore. We watched her for a total of 2 hours.
Observed from distance for 30 minutes, lost sight. Walking E.

Walked along the coast W direction from Holmiabukta. Staryed s. Rounded the spit into Fuglefjorden. Lost her for 5 miniutes, and found her swimming in the water with black thing next to her. Swimming, eating a geese chick. Took approx 20 seconds. Continued to pursue parent Barnacle Goose with one chick left. They tried to escape, but polar bear overtook chick in 30 seconds. Chick ducked, and polar bear ducked with it, came up with bird. Took it in its mouth, and ate it in another 20 seconds. Ignored parent goose, and continued swimming. Swam for the next 3 hours in between glacial brash ice. Attacked by terns and skua whenever closed in on islands. Landed on small island and went straight off the other side one time in the very beginning.

Overcast, small wind. Female bear on carcass of minky whale. Only spine left, dragged some 20 meters off the shore and over the beach top, making it difficult to observe her from zodiacs. She kept eating for the duration we stayed. 14:00 until 17:00. Another bear about 1000 meter SW of her. Walking NE along shore when we saw it for 5 minutes, then it laid down inland for the duration of our stay.

Watched male bear # 1 quite close. He was in the first band of pack ice, 9/10. Walking around as we approached, but then quickly laid down. Stayed down for several hours, until it got up and started walking towards bear # 2. It did a loop to the right before it approached bear # 2. They fought a bit. then ate together, fought some more, ate together, fought some more, ate together. One of them started walking away. Bear # 2 in the distance killed a seal as we approached bear # 1. It was too far into 10/10 ice so we could not go gloser.
